<emphasis id="7EF0A846FFCEFFFFFF64F97708651491" bold="true" box="[189,304,1724,1750]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C3B7454FFCEFFF0FF64F9210BDE1301" blockId="7.[189,1401,1770,1972]" lastBlockId="8.[189,1398,265,326]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<bibRefCitation id="281509A5FFCEFFFFFF64F9210B791543" author="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz" box="[189,556,1770,1796]" firstAuthor="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 141" refId="ref23560" refString="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz M. 2007. A revision of the family Typhlotanaidae Sieg 1984 (Crustacea: Tanaidacea) with the remarks on the Nototanaidae Sieg, 1976. Zootaxa 1598: 1 - 141. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1598.1.1" type="journal article" year="2007">Błażewicz-Paszkowycz (2007)</bibRefCitation>
revised the family in a large monograph, which described five new genera and 13 new species, as well as grouped species sharing a set of unique characters in seven ‘morpho-groups’ within 
<taxonomicName id="8B840FD7FFCEFFFFFE28F8FB0BDF150D" authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1882" box="[497,650,1840,1866]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Typhlotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7EF0A846FFCEFFFFFE28F8FB0BDF150D" box="[497,650,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Typhlotanais</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g. ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="8B840FD7FFCEFFFFFD31F8FB0ACB150D" authorityName="Shiino" authorityYear="1970" box="[744,926,1840,1866]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Typhlotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="greenwichensis">
<emphasis id="7EF0A846FFCEFFFFFD31F8FB0ACB150D" box="[744,926,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">greenwichensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ group, ‘mixtus’ group, ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="8B840FD7FFCEFFFFFB34F8FB0C3A150D" authorityName="Hansen" authorityYear="1913" box="[1261,1391,1840,1866]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Typhlotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinicauda">
<emphasis id="7EF0A846FFCEFFFFFB34F8FB0C3A150D" box="[1261,1391,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">spinicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ group, ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="8B840FD7FFCEFFFFFEC2F89F08D6152A" baseAuthorityName="Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[283,387,1876,1901]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Typhlotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis id="7EF0A846FFCEFFFFFEC2F89F08D6152A" box="[283,387,1876,1901]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">cornutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ group, ‘plicatus’ group, ‘eximius’ group, and ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="8B840FD7FFCEFFFFFC6CF89F0D62152A" authorityName="Hansen" authorityYear="1913" box="[949,1079,1876,1901]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Typhlotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trispinosus">
<emphasis id="7EF0A846FFCEFFFFFC6CF89F0D62152A" box="[949,1079,1876,1901]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">trispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ group. Characters of each ‘morpho-group’ are mentioned when comparing to new species described herein. It is assumed that the ‘morpho-groups’ may constitute new genera, but this must be further analyzed with a phylogenetic study. However, some typhlotanaids were neither classified under any previously established genera nor included in the morpho-groups created.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C3B7454FFC1FFF0FF64FEA50D33101C" blockId="8.[188,1399,366,603]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="281509A5FFC1FFF0FE82FEA50B9D13CF" author="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz" box="[347,712,366,392]" firstAuthor="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 141" refId="ref23560" refString="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz M. 2007. A revision of the family Typhlotanaidae Sieg 1984 (Crustacea: Tanaidacea) with the remarks on the Nototanaidae Sieg, 1976. Zootaxa 1598: 1 - 141. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1598.1.1" type="journal article" year="2007">Błażewicz-Paszkowycz (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8B840FD7FFC1FFF0FD0BFEA50A3E13CF" authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1882" box="[722,875,366,392]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Typhlotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="7EF0A846FFC1FFF0FD0BFEA50A3E13CF" box="[722,875,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Typhlotanais</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="65C3153DFFC1FFF0FCA9FEA50D5713CF" box="[880,1026,366,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
comprises only the 
<typeStatus id="933FCAF6FFC1FFF0FB30FEA50C4913CF" box="[1257,1308,366,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="8B840FD7FFC1FFF0FF65FE590B6313EB" authority="(Lilljeborg, 1864)" baseAuthorityName="Lilljeborg" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[188,566,401,428]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Typhlotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequiremis">
<emphasis id="7EF0A846FFC1FFF0FF65FE59080913EC" box="[188,348,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">T. aequiremis</emphasis>
(Lilljeborg, 1864)
</taxonomicName>
and all other species temporarily classified as 
<taxonomicName id="8B840FD7FFC1FFF0FB80FE5A0DA713EC" authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1882" box="[1113,1266,401,427]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Typhlotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis id="7EF0A846FFC1FFF0FB80FE5A0DA713EC" box="[1113,1266,401,427]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Typhlotanais</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="65C3153DFFC1FFF0FB20FE5A0C3A13EC" box="[1273,1391,401,427]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" sensu="lato">sensu lato</taxonomicNameLabel>
, showing large variation in characters as the pereonite-1 ratio (length to width), the number of setae on cheliped carpus dorsal margin setation, the form of mandible molar process form, and the shape of pereopods 1–3 basis shape. 
<taxonomicName id="8B840FD7FFC1FFF0FDD7FE310BF21053" authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1882" box="[526,679,506,532]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Typhlotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7EF0A846FFC1FFF0FDD7FE310BF21053" box="[526,679,506,532]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Typhlotanais</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most speciose genus of the family with 48 described species and a recent unpublished morphological phylogeny encompassing the family 
<taxonomicName id="8B840FD7FFC1FFF0FB1BFDD50C23107F" authorityName="Sieg" authorityYear="1984" box="[1218,1398,542,568]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Typhlotanaidae</taxonomicName>
suggests it is a polyphyletic group (
<bibRefCitation id="281509A5FFC1FFF0FD85FD8A0A40101C" author="Segadilha J. L." box="[604,789,577,603]" journalOrPublisher="Museu Nacional, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref24853" refString="Segadilha J. L. 2019. Sistematica da Familia Typhlotanaidae (Crustacea, Tanaidacea, Tanaidomorpha), Incluindo a Taxonomia das Especies do Brasil. Museu Nacional, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro." title="Sistematica da Familia Typhlotanaidae (Crustacea, Tanaidacea, Tanaidomorpha), Incluindo a Taxonomia das Especies do Brasil" type="book" year="2019">Segadilha 2019</bibRefCitation>
) that badly needs a revision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
